        <num>CC 3280</num>
        <heading>3280.  Mortgage is an indivisible real right</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3280.  Mortgage is an indivisible real right
Mortgage is an indivisible real right that burdens the entirety of the mortgaged property and that follows the property into whatever hands the property may pass.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
